==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Santalum
<hw>San"ta*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Sandalwood</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of trees with
entire opposite leaves and small apetalous flowers. There are less than
a dozen species, occurring from India to Australia and the Pacific
Islands. See <er>Sandalwood</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

